      <c01 level="series">
        <did>
          <unittitle>Family Papers</unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>The Family Papers series (0.2 linear feet) is comprised largely of records dealing with the history of the families of Otto and Alice Haisley. There is substantial information documenting the history of Alice Haisley's family, on her father's side (Callender and Winslow) and on her mother's side (Sowers). Undated notes trace the Callender family back to the 18th century, and other materials trace the origins of the names. Similarly detailed evidence is available for the Haisley family and its precursors (e.g. Hiatt and Rush). Virtually all the "Callender Family Correspondence" deals with the history of the Callender and Winslow families, whereas the "Haisley Family Correspondence," consists of letters Otto wrote to his mother while he was teaching in San Antonio. Also included in this series are obituaries following Haisley's death in 1959.</p>
        </scopecontent>
